Érd railway station is located in Pest County, in the central part of the city. It lies along the main railway line between Budapest and Székesfehérvár, making it an important stop both for long-distance trains heading toward Lake Balaton and for suburban commuters traveling to the capital.

The railway line was built in the late 19th century, and Érd has been a part of regional and suburban traffic ever since. Both passenger and InterCity trains stop here, offering direct connections to several major cities.

The station has been modernized, with multiple platforms and tracks. It handles a high volume of traffic, especially during morning and afternoon peak hours. Thanks to its central location, it’s easily accessible from all parts of the city and plays an important role in the region’s public transport.